race.description: House Of Arras Corporate Marquee Mdn Plate
race.comment: FIERCE 'N FABULOUS (13) switched from a top Victorian yard and made an immediate impact when finding a place here over 1100m. Keeps the premier hoop, and she will have taken fitness and learning. She will hit the line hard over the longer sprint. NIKOLSKY (10) switched from a South Australian barn and was narrowly beaten here first up over this trip. They have got her going well, and she's placed second-up. She also draws awkwardly, but gets a key jockey switch to Newitt and won't have to improve much to threaten. THERMAL MISS (14) debuts and went close in a recent Elwick trial. Has a 1.5kg claim for an in-form apprentice, and the inside gate should advantage. Looks to have some talent, and the betting will be key. TURFACTION (6) resumes and has switched from a Victorian yard. Has been off the scene for 205 days but has placed 2/3 fresh and has trialled twice. The betting will tell plenty with him as well.
